oks.google.co.in/books?id=uT-JPpeWKXMC&pg=PA153|title=Indian Youth, Problems and Prospects|last=Mohammad|first=Dr Noor|last2=Matin|first2=Abdul|date=1995|publisher=APH Publishing|isbn=9788170246497|language=en}}</ref>\n|\n|Samastha Kerala Sunni Yuvajana Samgam<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/news/india/kerala-muslim-outfit-to-open-100-schools-in-up-48221.html|title=Muslim outfit from Kerala will open 100 schools in UP-IndiaTV News|last=Desk|first=India TV News|date=5 March 2015|website=www.indiatvnews.com|language=en|access-date=23 August 2019}}</ref>\n|Sunni Yuvajana Federation\n([http://www.syfkerala.com/ ''website''])\n|Kerala Muslim Yuvajana Federation\n|-\n!Students' organizations\n|[[Samastha Kerala Sunni Students Federation]]\n|Kerala State Sunni Students' Federation\n([https://www.ssfkerala.org/ ''website''])\n|\n|Kerala Muslim Students Federation\n|}\n\n==Publications==\nSamastha's message is spread among the community through a number of [[publications]]. The educational board came to the publication field with the launch of ''Al-Bayan''<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=TC6zCAAAQBAJ&pg=PA330|title=Mappila Muslim Culture: How a Historic Muslim Community in India Has Blended Tradition and Modernity|last=Miller|first=Roland E.|date=27 April 2015|publisher=SUNY Press|isbn=9781438456010|location=|pages=330|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=-CLjAAAAMAAJ|title=Islam in Kerala: Groups and Movements in the 20th Century|last=Samad|first=M. Abdul|date=1998|publisher=Laurel Publications|isbn=|location=|pages=190|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=hzQKAQAAMAAJ|title=Emergence of Islam in Kerala in 20th century|last=Kurup|first=K. K. N.|last2=Ismail|first2=E.|last3=India)|first3=Maulana Abul Kalam Azad Institute of Asian Studies (Calcutta|date=2008|publisher=Standard Publishers (India)|isbn=|location=|pages=379|language=en}}</ref> monthly, first in [[Arabi Malayalam|Arabic Malayalam]] and then in [[Malayalam]] in 1954.\n\n==See also==\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://samastha.info/}}\n\n{{Islam in Kerala}}\n\n[[Category:Sunni Islam in India]]\n[[Category:Islam in Kerala]]\n[[Category:Defunct organisations based in India]]\n[[Category:Samastha]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\n{{short description|An Islamic organisation in India}}\n{{Infobox organization\n| name = \n| abbreviation = Samastha\n| merged = \n| successor = [[Dakshina Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama|Dakshina]] <small>(1955)</small><br />[[Kerala Samasthana Jamiyyathul Ulama|Samasthana]] <small>(1967)</small><br />EK faction <small>(1989)</small><br />AP faction <small>(1989)</small>\n| formation = \n| established = 1924\n| founders = [[Varakkal Mullokoya Thangal]]<br />[[Pangil Ahmed Kutty Musliyar]]\n| founding_location = [[Kozhikode]]\n| dissolved = 1989\n| merger = Akhila Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama\n| type = Islamic organisation\n| status = Registered in India as per Society Reg. Act.\n| purpose = \n| focus = \n| headquarters = [[Chelari]]\n| location = \n| region = [[Kerala]]\n| services = \n| language = [[Arabic]], [[Arabi Malayalam]]\n| sec_gen = \n| leader_title = Founding President\n| leader_name = [[Varakkal Mullokoya Thangal]]\n| leader_title2 = Founding Vice Presidents\n| leader_name2 = [[Pangil Ahmed Kutty Musliyar]]<br />Abul Haq Muhammad Abdul Bari<br />K. M. Abdul Qadir Musliyar<br />K. P. Muhammad Meeran Musliyar\n| leader_title3 = Founding Secretaries\n| leader_name3 = P. V. Muhammad Musliyar<br />P. K. Muhammad Musliyar\n| leader_title4 = \n| leader_name4 = \n| key_people = \n| publication = \n| subsidiaries = Sunni Yuvajana Sangham (SYS)<br />Samastha Kerala Jamiyyathul Muallimeen<br />[[Sunni Students' Federation]]<br />Sunni Bala Sangham\n| secessions = \n| affiliations = \n| formerly = Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama\n}}\n{{Islam}}\n\n'''Samastha''' (also called: '''Samastha Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama''') was a religious organisation of [[Muslim]] scholars and clerics formed in 1924 and registered in 1934 at the [[India|Indian]] state of [[Kerala]] headquartered at [[Kozhikode]], under the leadership of [[Varakkal Mullokoya Thangal]],<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=-CLjAAAAMAAJ|title=Islam in Kerala: Groups and Movements in the 20th Century|last=Samad|first=M. Abdul|date=1998|publisher=Laurel Publications|isbn=|location=|pages=132|language=en}}</ref> to resist the emergence of [[Salafi|Salafism]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=1RpuAAAAMAAJ|title=Muslims of Kerala: A Modern Approach|last=Sharafudeen|first=S.|date=2003|publisher=Kerala Historical Society|language=en}}</ref> and other Islamist ideologies<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=HbTXAAAAMAAJ|title=Mappila Muslims of Kerala: a study in Islamic trends|last=Miller|first=Roland E.|date=1992|publisher=Orient Longman|language=en|isbn=9780863112706}}</ref> in the Kerala.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books/about/Educational_Empowerment_of_Kerala_Muslim.html?id=PCBdogPnnqsC|title=Educational Empowerment of Kerala Muslims: A Socio-historical Perspective|last=Mohammed|first=U.|date=2007|publisher=Other Books|isbn=9788190388733|location=|pages=37|language=en}}</ref><ref>''Journal of Kerala studies'' [[University of Kerala]] 1982 - Volume 9 - Page 86 \"\"</ref><ref>''Journal of Kerala studies'' [[University of Kerala]] 1982 - Volume 9 - Page 86 \"Several religious and cultural organisations like Kerala Nadvatul Mujahideen, Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama, Samastha Kerala Jamiyathul Ulama and Jamaat-e-Islami established and continued to establish their own Madrasas. Each group ...\"</ref>{{Unreliable source?|date=August 2019}}<ref>{{Cite book|title=Kerala Muslims: a historical perspective|last=Engineer|first=Asghar Ali|date=1995|publisher=Ajanta Publications|isbn=9789996067372|location=Delhi|language=English|oclc=32890729}}</ref> \n\nIn the early days they worked together, but later they split into three groups. The [[:ml:\u0d15\u0d47\u0d30\u0d33 \u0d38\u0d02\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d25\u0d3e\u0d28 \u0d1c\u0d02\u0d07\u0d2f\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d7d \u0d09\u0d32\u0d2e|Kerala Samasthana Jamiyyathul Ulama]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.co.in/books?id=Jvh7DwAAQBAJ|title=Religious Imaginations: How Narratives of Faith are Shaping Today's World|last=Walters|first=James|date=15 December 2018|publisher=Gingko Library|isbn=9781909942233|language=en}}</ref> is created in 1967 and finally the Samastha EK Faction and Samastha AP Faction are splitted in 1989.<ref name=\"Naha\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/sunni-factions-to-bury-the-hatchet/article22466086.ece|title=Sunni factions to bury the hatchet|last=Naha|first=Abdul Latheef|date=18 January 2018|work=The Hindu|access-date=23 August 2019|language=en-IN|issn=0971-751X}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.news18.com/news/india/kerala-sunni-factions-start-mediations-after-three-decade-fight-1642581.html|title=Kerala Sunni Factions Start Mediations After Three-Decade Fight|website=News18|access-date=23 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://scroll.in/article/865455/big-deal-merger-of-two-factions-of-a-muslim-group-could-realign-political-forces-in-kerala|title=Big deal: Merger of two factions of a Muslim group could realign political forces in Kerala|last=Ameerudheen|first=T. A.|website=Scroll.in|language=en-US|access-date=23 August 2019}}</ref> The [[:ml:\u0d26\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d23 \u0d15\u0d47\u0d30\u0d33 \u0d1c\u0d02\u0d07\u0d2f\u0d4d\u0d2f\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d41\u0d7d \u0d09\u0d32\u0d2e|Dakshina Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama]] not a divided group but it was founded in 1955 with the blessings of the Samastha to expand the activities of Samastha in Cochin and Travancore.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/kozhikode/E-K-Sunnis-step-in-to-back-Kanthapuram-in-gender-row/articleshow/50019995.cms|title=E K Sunnis step in to back Kanthapuram in gender row {{!}} Kozhikode News - Times of India|last=3 Dec|first=TNN {{!}} Updated|last2=2015|website=The Times of India|language=en|access-date=10 July 2019|last3=Ist|first3=4:05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=PCBdogPnnqsC&pg|title=Educational Empowerment of Kerala Muslims: A Socio-historical Perspective|last=Mohammed|first=U.|date=2007|publisher=Other Books|isbn=9788190388733|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== History 1924-1989 ==\n\n=== Registration ===\nSamastha Kerala Jamiyyathul Ulama was formed on 26 June 1924, but it was officially registered on 14 November 1934, as the government approved its bylaw, which was agreed upon after deep and wide scholarly discussions held in various ''Mushawara'' meets and in consultation with law experts.  It promulgated the propagation of true Islam, impart of  education and activities against superstitions and un-Islamic traditions as its primary and supreme objectives.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Jvh7DwAAQBAJ|title=Religious Imaginations: How Narratives of Faith are Shaping Today's World|last=Walters|first=James|date=15 December 2018|publisher=Gingko Library|isbn=9781909942233|language=en}}</ref> Its bylaw also included encouragement for secular education compatible with religious beliefs, and calls for religious tolerance, interfaith friendship, peaceful existence and national progress.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.samasthabahrain.com/history.html|title=history.html|author=|date=|website=SamasthaBahrain.com|access-date=14 May 2017}}</ref> The registration number is S1.1934/35 at office of the Kozhikode district registrar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.samastha.net/samastha/samamain/index.php?page=shop.product_details&product_id=82&option=com_virtuemart&Itemid=53|title=samastha.net|author=|date=|website=Samastha.net|access-date=14 May 2017}}</ref>\n\n=== Mushawara (consulate body) ===\n\nThe Mushawara is the apex body of each Samastha organisations. There was only one Mushawara before the Samastha divides. After the split, each of the organisations has separate Mushawaras.<ref name=\"Naha\"/>\n\n=== The Leaders ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!No\n!Name\n!Tenure\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Presidents\n|-\n|1\n|[[Varakkal Mullokoya Thangal]]\n|1924-1933\n|-\n|2\n|[[Pangil Ahmed Kutty Musliyar]]\n|1933-1945\n|-\n|3\n|Valakkulam Abdul Bari Musliyar\n|1945-1965\n|-\n|4\n|KK Sadakkathullah Musliyar\n|1965-1967\n|-\n|5\n|[[Kanniyath Ahmed Musliyar]]\n|1967\u20131989\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |General secretaries\n|-\n|1\n|PV Muhammed Musliyar\n|1924\u20131951\n|-\n|2\n|Pravanna Mohiyadheen Kutty Musliyar\n|1951\u20131957\n|-\n|3\n|[[E. K. Aboobacker Musliyar]]\n|1957\u20131989\n|-\n! colspan=\"3\" |Other leaders\n|-\n|\n|[[Sayyid Abdur Rahman Bafaqi Thangal]]\n|xxxx\n|-\n|\n|Sayyid P.M.S.A Pookoya Thangal\n|xxxx\n|-\n|\n|[[Kutubi Muhammed Musliyar]]\n|xxxx\n|-\n|\n|Chappanangadi Bapu Musliyar\n|xxxx\n|-\n|\n|Kottumala Aboobacker Musliyar<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hindu.com/2011/05/12/stories/2011051262840300.htm |title=Archive News |publisher=The Hindu |date= |accessdate=1 December 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Behnegarsoft.com |url=http://www.taghribnews.com/vdca0ana.49n6m1gtk4.html |title=(TNA) - Every rennaisence endeavors in islam has to be achieved through unity among communities |publisher=Taghribnews |date= |accessdate=1 December 2016}}</ref>\n|xxxx\n|-\n|}\n\n=== Founding Mushawara members ===\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!No\n!Name\n!Member until\n!Other positions held\n|-\n|1\n|[[Varakkal Mullokoya Thangal]]\n|1933\n|President(1924-1933)\n|-\n|2\n|[[Pangil Ahmed Kutty Musliyar]]\n|1945\n|Vice President(1924-1933), President(1933-1945)\n|-\n|3\n|Valakkulam Abdul Bari Musliyar\n|1965\n|President(1945-1965)\n|-\n|4\n|KP Muhammed Meeran Musliyar\n|1947\n|Vice President(1924-yyyy)\n|-\n|5\n|KM Abdul Qadir Musliyar\n|\n|(1924-yyyy)\n|-\n|6\n|PV Mu